Susan X7 months ago on Google
3/5
Had a cold welcome to the hotel, the reception staff wasn’t the friendliest when we arrived. However, during our stay the rest of the staff were very attentive and friendly. …
Had a cold welcome to the hotel, the reception staff wasn’t the friendliest when we arrived. However, during our stay the rest of the staff were very attentive and friendly.
The room was comfortable and spacious, with a lot of storage and big baths & showers. We had a nice garden area outside as well. A kettle, coffee and tea was included in the room but you need to go to the bar to get milk.
As an all inclusive hotel, the food was varied and there was a lot of choice. The windows for the buffet are very reasonable and you can always go to the bar for snacks outside of those areas. There was a good selection in the drinks menu as well, but I would recommend sticking to the classics. We also ate at the Moroccan restaurant separate to the hotel (also included in the all-inclusive but you have to book) but it was average at best.
Finally, the lack of an indoor pool seems like a massive oversight, especially if you’re travelling in colder & rainier seasons. There is a heated outdoor pool but it’s not that warm. To use the indoor pool in the hotel, you have to pay around £14 via the spa.
Overall, it was a pleasant stay but a few things could be better.

Jonathan Sandforda week ago on Google
2/5
Beautifully present hotel and bedrooms immaculate and spacious. Delightful grounds all landscaped with 2 huge pools and plenty of sun beds. Entertainment at specific times. Nice gym included in cost. There is a health spa, this is extra …
Beautifully present hotel and bedrooms immaculate and spacious. Delightful grounds all landscaped with 2 huge pools and plenty of sun beds. Entertainment at specific times. Nice gym included in cost. There is a health spa, this is extra cost.
Food and drink all inclusive. Food superb, varied, fresh and well presented.
Staff generally very pleasant.
Be aware the hotel is in the middle of nowhere !!!! So no places to walk after dinner bar walking round in circle's on the development. taxis to everywhere required. There is subject to availability / limited times a free shuttle bus - check times out and return times.
In the evenings VERY mediocre entertainment/ sometimes a bit club 18/30 so generally disappointing and as I say nowhere to go.
Flies everywhere- so annoying round the pool and outside dining.
Not convinced I’d come back purely based on location but all in all excellent value for money.

Beki Swinfield2 months ago on Google
5/5
The most wonderful experience!
From the moment we walked through the doors, every possible effort was made to …
The most wonderful experience!
From the moment we walked through the doors, every possible effort was made to make our stay as relaxing as possible. The staff are incredibly attentive and never stop working, the hotel and gardens are immaculate and the rooms are spacious and well appointed. I absolutely loved all the small touches and personalised service like staff making efforts to remember your drink orders and make them without prompting.
There are a few small issues that should be considered: there weren't enough staff on the bars and no drinks are self service which led to queueing and the restaurant was often quite busy and might benefit from allocated time slots. Also, the hotel is situated a fair way outside of Marrakech with very little in walking distance around it so is best suited to those who plan minimal excursions. Several people have mentioned the food which is slightly repetitive but, even with my partner being a picky eater, we always found several options that we enjoyed; to each their own!
Overall, we had a truly fantastic experience and would be happy to return!

Corbmac McKay3 months ago on Google
5/5
One thing that needs to be clarified - this is by no means a five star hotel to European standards. However, this did not make me find my stay less enjoyable. The hotel is located about 20mins from Marrakech in the Palmeraie so there is no …
One thing that needs to be clarified - this is by no means a five star hotel to European standards. However, this did not make me find my stay less enjoyable. The hotel is located about 20mins from Marrakech in the Palmeraie so there is no noise disrupting the peace here.
The hotel is immaculate and the staff here are amongst the friendliest I’ve ever met on my world travels. Reflecting that this hotel is more meeting four star criteria, the food in the buffet is varied (and quite good), the drinks are plentiful (although the alcohol in the cocktails is minimal), and the evening entertainment is okay.
If you stay for more than four nights you will have a complimentary meal in the hotel restaurant. I didn’t enjoy my meal here and felt that the food in the buffet was of a higher standard and had more variety. The gym is good for a basic hotel gym, and the hotel offers several recreational activities to do throughout the day.
Big tip: if you want to avoid being disturbed by music throughout the day ask for a room that isn’t facing the pool!
All in all, a very enjoyable experience!

Gabe Dugo3 months ago on Google
3/5
Almost finished the stay here and for the most part the stay was good. The food is delicious with lots of variety and the pool area is great with lots of seating. …
Almost finished the stay here and for the most part the stay was good. The food is delicious with lots of variety and the pool area is great with lots of seating.
The bed is comfortable, but the room had AC problems and TV problems too. The tv channels in our room were not always clear and would freeze at times, this is because they use an antenna network for their TV. There are no American/Canadian network channels for anyone who is visiting from those places and looking to stay updated with the news happening over there.
For the AC, we had it set at 18 degrees Celsius for three days to try to bring the temperature down in the room and it wouldn’t go below 24 degrees, it made for some hot and uncomfortable nights of sleeping. The guest services kept sending people to fix it but they always said it was working fine. One maintenance worker, left the vent open and the ladder in our room for a couple of hours. In the end, we gave up trying to fix it as no one seemed to know how to fix it.
Overall, it was a decent stay but I wouldn’t recommend it as a 5 star resort in international standards.

H C4 months ago on Google
2/5
We stayed here for 10 nights and it's our last night tonight. We are so disappointed with this hotel, please do not waste your money or holiday here!
The hotel advertises itself as a 5* luxery resort and we were foolishly excited …
We stayed here for 10 nights and it's our last night tonight. We are so disappointed with this hotel, please do not waste your money or holiday here!
The hotel advertises itself as a 5* luxery resort and we were foolishly excited to stay here.
On our first night, we were put into a connecting room and could hear everything our neighbours were saying and doing. We were moved to a 'quieter room' but there's no sleeping in this hotel as they play loud, thumping music until midnight. We complained on several occasions but we were told they wouldn't turn it down, honestly it's like being above a club!
The cocktails are also very bad. The booze is watered down and we watched throughout our stay the bar staff putting incorrect spirits into cocktails. They even ran out of spirits one night and we watched staff pretend to put spirits into guests cocktails to fool guests.
The restaurant food is great and the restaurant staff are brilliant. The buffet food has variety but unfortunately that doesn't stretch to the rest of the hotel, the snack bar serves chicken nuggets on the ceaser salad and you eat your chicken nugget ceaser salad listening to ridiculous club music at midday (the snack bar is by the loud pool).
Despite this, the grounds are beautiful, the gym is okay, rooms are clean and the shuttle bus is free so you have easy access to the center which is good.
We remain disappointed with management, the music is so loud and all we asked for was for the music to be turned down slightly so we could sleep. The hotel does not cater for or offer solutions to guests who wish to sleep before midnight.
-If cheap booze, loud music and no sleep is the holiday you want from your 5* stay, then this is the hotel for you.
-If you want to relax, eat and drink quality food/drink and sleep well please avoid!

Service2.0

Nice stay in Marrakech. Two pools with different vibes. One relaxed, the other more energetic. Bars understaffed but staff do their best and are friendly. Suites are a good size, clean and comfortable. Pool suites probably a bit of a gimmick. Wi-Fi didn’t work for two days but that was kind of nice to be honest. Food was ok, got a bit samey after a week, but it was always fresh and well presented. Free shuttle into the city if you want to go and explore, or it’s easy to book a taxi. Plenty of bottled water made available. Quite a few activities if you’re into that sort of thing. Spa was well received, although this is an extra cost.

Hannah Cook2 months ago on Google
4/5
Stayed here for 5 nights with my boyfriend - we had a lovely stay.
Room was spotless, grounds of the hotel were very well kept, all staff were also nice and attentive - especially the entertainment staff. Drinks were good in …
Stayed here for 5 nights with my boyfriend - we had a lovely stay.
Room was spotless, grounds of the hotel were very well kept, all staff were also nice and attentive - especially the entertainment staff. Drinks were good in the day and in the lobby bar on the evening - depsite this line could get very long and out the door to wait for a drink.
Food was good, as other reviews say also, the meals (breakfast lunch and dinner) were a bit repetitive but was always something for everyone.
As a vegeterian, I struggled with the food not being labelled vegeterian or not. I arent usually one to pick up on things like this but on 2 occasions I bit into food with meat in - that looked like they didnt contain meat.
Read a couple of reviews about things being stolen by cleaners - we did not have an issue with this and the cleaners we did come into contact with were very nice.
We got money changed at the hotel using the cash point - was easy and good exchange rate. Booking trips through the hotel was also easy and I would recommend doing that.
Didnt go to the Moroccan restaurant as the menu was to a very aquired taste.
Check in was chaotic - lots of people arrived at once. Not the hotels fault but perhaps could have been handled better. No option to anyone for an early check in which was unfortunate.
Overall, I would recommend this hotel. Only slight things that could have been improved on.

Sadiea month ago on Google
4/5
We have just returned from our stay, and overall it was ok.

We have just returned from our stay, and overall it was ok.
In terms of the hotel itself, facilities are great, two choices of pools, a quieter one and one with more activities going on. The spa has a lot on offer, however you are invited to spend £100s which of course is their job really to upsell! The room was lovely and clean, very pretty and the bed and shower were great, however we had an ant problem in our room. Reported but nothing really seemed to change.
In terms of the food it was pretty standard hotel buffet food, plenty of choice, some repeats, some really great tasting food, some not so good! We visited the a la carte restaurant one night and honestly wished we hadn't! The food was absolutely horrendous! It was a set menu, there was very little choice and what did arrive was dry, and just yuck. I have to say that we were very disappointed and it was a shame because the staff there were quite lovely.
In terms of the other staff, reception and the bell boys were friendly but the majority of the rest of the staff were rude, didn't interact with you and had no customer service skills. This is all apart from Azdine who was absolutely exceptional, so attentive and kind he was by far the best staff member there. That being said, part of me wonders if this was because we are English and we often saw them engaging in conversations with French holidaymakers (who knew they spoke French in Morocco!). The behaviour of fellow English holidaymakers also makes me think this could be the reason why. I felt ambarrassed to be English whilst we were there due to the rude and childish behaviour of fellow guests.
In terms of the entertainment, they had a lovely couple singing acoustically until around 10pm each evening, which was great, however post 10pm it got extremely loud, and we were very close to the entertainment area outside so could hear word for word which at 12am after a long day is not really ideal.
Overall we had an ok stay, enjoyed some cocktails, and the sun, but ultimately wouldn't return.

Jodie Blunt2 months ago on Google
5/5
The hotel was beautiful and spotless as well as our room, with maids coming in every day to mop, change towels and provide fresh supplies. The air con was a dream especially when it came to afternoon naps out of the 42 degree heat! Wifi …
The hotel was beautiful and spotless as well as our room, with maids coming in every day to mop, change towels and provide fresh supplies. The air con was a dream especially when it came to afternoon naps out of the 42 degree heat! Wifi also reached all areas of the hotel we went to. The hairdryer wasn’t very powerful though so I wouldn’t pin your hopes on using this.
Food in the buffet hall was delicious, with a large variety from breakfast pastries and omelettes made to order, pizza, pasta and salads to traditional Moroccan tagine, cous cous, lentils etc. so lots to pick from. We especially enjoyed the dessert and ice cream selection which changed every meal time! We booked a night into the restaurant and had the vegetarian option, the atmosphere and service was great but the food was just as good as the main buffet so we wouldn’t rush back to the restaurant but it was a nice experience. The snack bar was also handy if you missed the buffet and the chicken caesar burger was delicious!
During the day there are two pools, one fairly quiet with the swim up bar helpful if you want to just relax and read a book. Then there is an activity pool which plays music and has a range of activities around to get involved in, varied on a rota. Staff invite you to get involved and let you know what’s coming up but don’t pester you at all so you can still relax at this pool. Big thank you to the animation team Emma, Zizu, Titif and Mohammed for making us feel so welcome and being so lovely! We never struggled to get a sun lounger or parasol but if you wanted one of the egg chairs or day beds with padded cushions you’d have to be out early (7:30am ish) to put a towel down.
Azdine the evening waiter was always smiling even though he can be rushed off his feet, he seemed to recognise us and what drinks we usually ordered. He provided amazing service and was attentive throughout our stay.
Evening entertainment is fantastic and varied, it’s all outside and we always managed to have somewhere to sit but it meant moving furniture from other parts of the hotel so it would be worth reconsidering the evening entertainment space. The cocktails are very weak in alcohol but still tasty, especially the Marrakech Flower that Azdine recommended!
There’s plenty to do in the hotel but if you wanted to explore the city it’s only about 20 minutes to the centre. The hotel had a free shuttle bus to and from the centre each day which you’d need to reserve in advance, they also have an ATM and two shops to buy souvenirs, sun cream and other supplies. They also help with excursions and book any taxis for you that you may need, we got a taxi to Menara Mall which cost 150 MAD each way (£12.50).
For context we are two mid-20s friends (girls) who came on a week long trip and loved every minute. There were quite a lot of couples on this trip but also some small friends and family groups so it seems ideal for anyone. Thank you all!

Very disappointed with this resort to say the least. I waited almost to the end of my stay to write my review in case I changed my mind and gave an unfair review. To my sadness, things didn’t get any better. …
Very disappointed with this resort to say the least. I waited almost to the end of my stay to write my review in case I changed my mind and gave an unfair review. To my sadness, things didn’t get any better.
At first sight the resort looks nice, the groundings are well kept and the rooms are spotless (Thumbs up for that!!) but the longer you stay the more you notice their lack of understanding of “in all inclusive” as the mini fridge in the room only has 1 bottle of water. As all inclusive, I would expect to have drinks available in my room.
Right at the entrance of the lobby is a metal detector which to some maybe a reassurance of safety, but it made me wonder the likelihood of an attack.
The resort transpire lots of rules and didn’t feel very relaxed at times. Be aware that restaurant open a bit later for dinner on Sundays/Monday and there isn’t anywhere else to get food from 6 til 7:30, not ideal for people who like to have early dinner. I would recommend Management to rethink this.
The bar staff by the heated pool can do with a better customer service, but overall the staff are friendly and professional.
There is free Wi-Fi but it doesn’t work well in the bedroom I stayed in. It was a good opportunity to disconnect, but if you are looking for good speed internet, you may need to do a bit of research for other resorts
Overall the experience was ok so 3 stars

I had a great stay. The staff is outstanding and go the extra mile for their guests. Mainly the guys at bar pool - Youness, Ayoub, Unis and Hamza. Beautiful and tasty coffees in the morning. Definitely would go back.

Lesley Brophy3 years ago on Google
4/5
Just back from a 4 night break over Christmas. Have to say the hotel is spotless and the beds are extremely comfortable and the bathroom had a huge walk in shower that was really fab. The decor in the hotel is definitely not 5 star as it's …
Just back from a 4 night break over Christmas. Have to say the hotel is spotless and the beds are extremely comfortable and the bathroom had a huge walk in shower that was really fab. The decor in the hotel is definitely not 5 star as it's all very modern and minimalist. There was a good choice in the buffet restaurant, but most of the dishes weren't labelled, so you didn't know if it was fish or meat as a lot of the dishes were in pastry or breadcrumbs. As I'm allergic to seafood and shell fish, this was quite annoying. Also I didn't like the fact that you couldn't get your own drinks like a lot of all inclusive hotels I have stayed in, you have to wait for a waiter/waitress to come and take your order, not ideal when it's busy. I would go back to this hotel, but I would rate it as a decent 4 star.

I stayed here last summer (end of june), honestly one of the nicest hotels I've stayed at, the site is very new, perfect for a relaxing and romantic get aways. The staff were exceptional and always on hand to help. My girlfriend called ahead due to it being my birthday and asked for a cake and balloons to be put in the room before, for a small fee they really did go above and beyond.
They provide a free shuttle bus into the city centre which is completley worth doing.
The spa experience on site was very good and both my girlfriend and I enjoyed the experience thoroughly.
Evening entertainment is different each night and all inclusive drinks keep flowing.
We also took a trip to Nikki beach and the staff were very helpful in booking taxis and giving advise.
The younger staff that organised day time entertainment, archery, pool yoga and exercises classes etc. were very enthusiastic, friendly and made an effort to keep you happy.
Food buffet and bar food was very nice and had something for everyone, even fussy eaters!
Overall I would go back to this hotel based on my last experience thank you Be Live Collection Marrakech!

Anthony H2 years ago on Google
3/5
This is a clean and modern hotel. We stayed all inclusive and the food was generally varied and quite good. There are activities to keep you busy, such as yoga, gym, archery, ping pong, pool. The spa is extra money. …
This is a clean and modern hotel. We stayed all inclusive and the food was generally varied and quite good. There are activities to keep you busy, such as yoga, gym, archery, ping pong, pool. The spa is extra money.
There are two pools (three if you include the one in the spa). One is gently heated and the other is not. The heated one is roughly 25 metres and is suitable for some exercise (as well as relaxation).
The staff are mostly pleasant, friendly, talkative and helpful. On one occasion however, one staff member did display casual racism; he asked me where I (an east asian) came from and then proceeded to pull his eyes apart! Customs are different in Morocco, so my reaction is different to if it was in the UK. Still, I expected better from a hotel welcoming international guests. Docking at least a star for that alone.

An excellent adult only hotel with great facilities, delicious local food on tap, fantastic staff who go out of their way to make you feel at home away from home!
Advertised as 'Marrakech' its actually located slightly out of the city - in Annakhil - so don't be surprised if your journey from the airport takes up to 25 minutes.
Lots to do when you're on site and even more adventures to be had off site: trips to the Medinna, the Atlas mountains among others, and my favourite: a trip to Chez Ali for a spectacular night of horsemanship, Bedouin singing, dancing and eating.
All in all, Be Live Collection for Adults is a keeper. Get out there and see for yourself.

Dean Rippon3 years ago on Google
3/5
Firstly I would like to explain why this hotel is not a 5* hotel.
1) The service is generally poor and not attentive, for example at breakfast you need to ask for a drink and if you are lucky you may get a smile. Bowls and …
Firstly I would like to explain why this hotel is not a 5* hotel.
1) The service is generally poor and not attentive, for example at breakfast you need to ask for a drink and if you are lucky you may get a smile. Bowls and glasses are at a shortage which for a self claimed 5* resort is shocking.
2) When you enter the Buffet restaurant as with all 5* hotels you would expect to be taken to a free table? Well not here, you need to walk around the restaurant and find one yourself. Then wait, and wait and wait to ask a waiter/ress for a drink.
3) No glasses at the snack bar usually in the afternoon. They can't cope with the washing up.
4) No mini bar in the room. You will also be informed it is forbidden to take drinks in your room?
5) The breakfast is OK, pretty standard. Lunch is the best meal of the day in the Buffet restaurant. Dinner is poor, very very poor. Unless you eat pasta and pizza your choice is limited. The morrocan selection is poor. The food is warm at best. The pasta is the best option but I didn't come to Morroco to eat pasta.
If you have food allergies or like me can't eat bread you will be struggling to eat. No food allergy advise on any food and cross contamination on many food types.
The snack bar is OK again if you want to eat pizza and burgers and fries. I don't travel to 5* resorts and want this, I expect more. The salads are limited and don't expect to eat one past 16.00 as you be told they are not available?
The Ksar restaurant is not too bad. You can have one reservation per stay if you stop over 4 nights.
6) They have a strange card system for the towels. You have to pay £90 deposit for 2 shabby looking brown towels. We took our own and glad we did. When you return them they give you a card with a number on. Return this for you deposit.
I am not just moaning on but the service and food is that of a 3* hotel, at best.
The positives are:
The rooms are really nice and spotless, beds are large and very comfy. We stopped in 4004 ground floor next to the snack bar. The swim up rooms are more of a selling gimic. You can't swim up you could however walk up to your room in water?
The bus to the city is useful and free. We used this twice. A little tip. Go in the morning if you want to shop. Hardly anyone bothers you. Go at night to experience the hustle and bustle.
The pools and pool staff are good, staff are very friendly.
Grounds are kept nice and clean.
The coffee is good as is the Morrocan tea.
There is now where to have a nice afternoon coffee and cake or light snack.
I have travelled all over the world and have been lucky to stay in some top hotels. I stay away a lot with work so I am used to the hotel life.
My wife and I have had a relaxing time away from our children for a week. I wouldn't return back to this hotel or even Morroco. It was an experience but not one I will be having again.
One last thing, the evening entertainment was at best average. After a week with most hotel entertainment you loose the will to live.
Go to Turkey for 5* service, fresh food, culture.
Cheers.

Lyndsey Worthy4 years ago on Google
4/5
Lovely all inclusive hotel. Stunning rooms and a lovely layout. The buffet could be improved somewhat but still provided enough choice to cater for a variety of guests. As a visitor on a company reward trip with colleagues, the concept of a …
Lovely all inclusive hotel. Stunning rooms and a lovely layout. The buffet could be improved somewhat but still provided enough choice to cater for a variety of guests. As a visitor on a company reward trip with colleagues, the concept of a window into the bathroom from the bedroom is not the greatest architectural plan. If you plan on travelling with friends or colleagues, just be aware you're going to need to work out a shower schedule!
The location was close enough to the town and the hotel provides a taxi and shuttle service you can take advantage of. I would reccomend changing your money back and forth at your hotel as this is a guaranteed location for exchange. I would reccomend this hotel for anyone wishing to visit Marrakech for a long weekend.

Daniel Blanchard4 years ago on Google
5/5
Very nice hotel and well looked after.
There are 2 pools, one with activities like Zumba or archery and music …
Very nice hotel and well looked after.
There are 2 pools, one with activities like Zumba or archery and music throughout the day and the other a relaxation pool with no music and a swim up pool bar.
There is a free shuttle bus into the Medina throughout the day which needs to be booked the day before.
There are various bars in the hotel which open at different times but mean you can just about always get a drink and/or food.
There is a small shop inside the hotel which sells some souvineers, sweets, cigarettes etc.
There is also an ATM located in the hotel reception and you can exchange cash behind reception.

Tommy Anthonissen3 years ago on Google
4/5
The hotel is quite remote, but the hotel resolves this easily this with a (free) shuttle to the city center.
1) The hotel: …
The hotel is quite remote, but the hotel resolves this easily this with a (free) shuttle to the city center.
1) The hotel:
a. Room: we've had a swim up room. Heavens! Every morning and evening relaxing at your own pool brings the holy in holiday.
b. Swimming pools: there are 2 outside pools. A "vivid" one and a "relaxing" one.
The animation is enjoyable and tries to make everyone happy with a various program during the day (but is quite the same every day)
c. Personnel: the warmth, the politeness, the willingness to help, ... Bravo: everybody tries to make from your holiday a glorious time.
d. Drinking: it's an all-inclusive hotel which logically means that you can drink what you want. But the bar(wo)men try to make from each cocktail a good cocktail. Plus: they have healthy smoothies in the all-in formula. If you want 🍾: you have to pay per bottle.
e. Eating: if you book minimum 5nights you may eat in the Moroccan restaurant. If not, you can enjoy the varied buffet (breakfast, lunch and dinner). We've read a lot before our departure about the eating. Our proper experience is that you've got your classic pasta/pizza (showcooking!) for those who miss their Domino's too much, but for those who appreciate the local cuisine the chef's prepare a nice variety. Yes, the food is very good and yes sometimes it's a bit cold, but nevertheless: YUM! PS: Do not pass the dessertcounter blindly = YUM part 2. PS2: Every morning freshly showbaked pancakes, please try the Moroccan waffles (with a bit of honey) = YUM part 3!!
2) The Spa:
a. Treatments: the ladies over there they treat you like kings and queens. Their main task is to make you feel relax: they succeed gloriously.
b. Personnel: The spa manager (the only man we saw) doesn't give you that relaxing feeling. He gives you the feeling that his only task is selling. We've made a complaint to the PR-Desk (thank you) and they've found a solution and the man apologized sincerely.
Generally: Relax and enjoy the Moroccan hospitality! Thank you, Merci, Shukraan 🐼❣️

Laura Lallement3 months ago on Google

(Translated by Google) A week's stay overall very good.
- Very clean hotel, well decorated and carefully maintained exteriors. …
(Translated by Google) A week's stay overall very good.
- Very clean hotel, well decorated and carefully maintained exteriors.
- Spacious room but we regretted the absence of cotton swabs and bathrobes (the more expensive rooms have them)
Be careful if you want to sleep because it seems that the maids clean all the time (even at 11 p.m. above your room)
- The relaxation pool is great but would need a good refresh (tiles are coming off and the joints are dirty)
Too bad to let people smoke there.
- The buffet is very good, unfortunately keeping food warm leaves something to be desired.
- The staff are charming, polite and pleasant (with a few exceptions).
- Be careful if you book transfers to and from the airport! We were totally puffed up! €25 one way and €35 ​​return!
- The drivers of the free shuttles to go to the city center are badly behaved, do not answer when you say "hello" to them and pull the face. That's a shame !
Besides, be careful when you get off the bus, people jump on you (don't even let them get out of the bus) and offer to guide you through Marrakech for a fee.
Real vultures!
(Original)
Séjour d'une semaine globalement très bien.
- Hôtel très propre, bien décoré et extérieurs entretenus avec soin.
- Chambre spacieuse mais nous avons déploré l'absence de cotons tiges et peignoirs de bain (les chambres plus chères en ont)
Attention si vous voulez dormir car il semble que les femmes de chambre fassent le ménage n'importe quand (même à 23h au dessus de votre chambre)
- La piscine détente est super mais nécessiterait un bon rafraîchissement (des carreaux se détachent et les joints sont sales)
Dommage de laisser les gens y fumer.
- Le buffet est très bien, malheureusement le maintien au chaud des aliments laisse à désirer.
- Le personnel est charmant, poli et agréable (à quelques exceptions près).
- Attention si vous réservez des transferts depuis et vers l'aéroport ! On nous a carrément enflés ! 25€ l'aller et 35€ le retour !
- Les chauffeurs des navettes gratuites pour aller au centre ville sont mal élevés, ne répondent pas quand on leur dit "bonjour" et tire la tronche. C'est dommage !
D'ailleurs attention quand vous descendez du bus, des personnes vous sautent dessus (ne laisse même pas sortir du bus) et vous proposent de vous guider dans Marrakech moyennant finances.
De véritables vautours !

It has a shower and bathtub, it has a large window that overlooks the rest of the room.
It is wonderful to have a drink at night on the terrace of the room while you put your feet in the pool lying on the hammock. A delight!
The service in general is very good, although I must put the downside that despite not having long queues in bars, restaurants and others. Sometimes they are a bit slow in putting the coffee, drink or glass that you have ordered.
For the rest, very nice and if you have any suggestions they do not hesitate to satisfy you.
I would like to highlight that the treatment of the waiter Azdine has been more than excellent, with just one look he knew what we wanted or needed, something very professional! Thank you Azdin!
The location is not bad either since there is a long free bus schedule that leaves you in the medina in 15/20 minutes and picks you up.
If it weren't for the buses, yes, it's a bit far from Marrakech. Come on, you're not going to leave the hotel.
I hope this helps people to decide to come to this hotel. I really recommend it and I'm sure you'll have a really good time!

¡Nos ha encantado este hotel!
Hemos pasado unas excelentes vacaciones donde hemos podido disfrutar de la comida y la bebida, de los grupos de música en directo y sobretodo descansar y relajarnos tanto en la piscina con bar, la piscina de deportes y animación y la piscina de la propia habitación!

El servicio en general muy bien, aunque debo de poner la pega de que a pesar de no haber grandes colas en bares, restaurantes y demas. A veces son algo lentos en ponerte el café, la bebida o la copa que hayas pedido.
Por lo demás, muy agradables y si tienes cualquier sugerencia no dudan en satisfacerte.
Me gustaría resaltar que el trato del camarero Azdine ha sido más que excelente, con solo una mirada sabía que es lo que queríamos o necesitabamos, algo muy profesional! ¡Gracias Azdine!
La ubicación tampoco está mal ya que hay un amplior horario de autobuses gratuitos que en 15/20 minutos te dejan en la medina y te recogen.
Si no fuese por los autobuses, si, esta algo lejos de Marrakech. Vamos que del hotel no vas a salir.

Despite my great satisfaction with the staff, the welcome or the beauty of the hotel .. I must admit that there are still a few small negative points to highlight .. especially with regard to the all-you-can-eat buffet .. the quality of the Food was mediocre .. apart from breakfast I did not enjoy the meals too much !!
The rooms were beautiful and spacious, but they lacked amenities, no bathrobe or slippers in the bathrooms .. (remember that it is a 5 * hotel) no drawers either and the hair dryer did not work not very good and was of very poor quality! (Well these are just small details for me)
last thing, it concerns the location of the hotel .. a little far from the center of Marrakech .. but the hotel offers us a free shuttle .. so in the end it is fine ..
In short, in summary all that I have just mentioned are small details, despite everything we fell in love with this hotel and particularly for the staff!
(Original)
Je met 5 Étoiles pour le personnel et le service qui sont irréprochable ! Grâce à eux nous avons passé un petit séjour inoubliable (malgré que nous étions dans l’obligation de l’écourter à cause de la décision de dernière minute concernant la suspension des vols entre le Maroc et la France).. mais ce n’est que partie remise, nous y retournerons probablement .. car cet hôtel est tout simplement sublime autant à l’intérieur qu’à l’extérieur ! Il y a 3 piscines, des soirées, plein d’activités, on s’y sent tellement bien !
Merci infiniment à tout le personnel de l’hôtel qui sont d’une gentillesse extrême.. !
Malgré ma grande satisfaction concernant le personnel, l’accueil ou la beauté de l’hôtel .. je dois avouer qu’il y a quand même quelques petits points négatifs a souligner .. notamment par rapport au buffet à volonté .. la qualité des plats était médiocre .. hormis le petit déjeuner je n’ai pas trop appréciée les repas !!
Les chambres étaient belles et spacieuses, mais ça manqué d’équipements, pas de peignoir ni de chaussons dans les salles de bain .. (je rappelle que c’est un hôtel 5*) pas de tiroirs non plus et le sèche cheveux ne fonctionnait pas très bien et était de très mauvaise qualité! (Bon ce ne sont que des petits détails pour moi)
dernière chose, ça concerne l’emplacement de l’hôtel .. un peu éloigné du centre de Marrakech .. mais l’hôtel nous propose une navette gratuite.. donc finalement ça passe ..
Bref en résumé tous que je viens de cité ce sont des petits détails, malgré tout on a eu un reel coup de cœur pour cet hôtel et particulièrement pour le personnel !

Un buffet très varié pour les 3 repas (petit déj, déj et dinner). Deux piscines splendides avec un pool bar pour les boissons, jus, etc.
Des chambres spacieuses et ergonomiques, un très grand lit super confortable, TV, une grande baignoire, un balcon, la climatisation est vraiment silencieuse.
Une petite remarque : Les chaînes TV ne sont pas toutes opérationnelles et il faut penser à rajouter d'autres chaînes surtout françaises au bouquet.
Nous reviendrons la prochaine fois sans hésitation.
Salut à Monsieur Abdellah et Madame Marwa pour leur accueil chaleureux.

Pas mal. Mais honnêtement, pour le prix, je suis un peu déçu.

Nicole Gouetché4 years ago on Google
3/5
(Translated by Google) My fiance and I spent the week of July 21-28, 2018 at this hotel.
Where to start ? …
(Translated by Google) My fiance and I spent the week of July 21-28, 2018 at this hotel.
Where to start ?
The rooms are good, consistent with the photos. The hotel is clean and new.
The spa is not bad, the masseuse is professional. The oils smell very good!
Theme evenings are organized every evening (when they take place, 3 evenings canceled over a week without it being announced) with singers in the first part. These may be the only good points.
On the other hand,
Cocktails are not cocktails but infamous liquid preparations. In a week I tried to taste them all and enjoy them again, hoping it was just a mistake from the bartender, but no. They are really filthy.
The food in the buffet restaurant is quite good but nothing exceptional, you should not be demanding, the desserts on the other hand are very average.
Regarding the staff, the waiters and receptionists are nice and try to do their best but the quality of service is average. We sometimes had to wait up to 30 minutes to get a table, or even a glass of water. Waiting for a glass of water in full heat, under 40 ° is really not great. Bottles should at least be given on arrival.
The experience was not disastrous. I would keep fond memories of it but the hotel is not worth its 5 stars at all ... Rather 2-3 at most.
I would definitely come back to Marrakech one day but not to this hotel.
(Original)
Mon fiancé et moi même avons passé la semaine du 21 au 28 juillet 2018 au sein de cet hôtel.
Par où commencer ?
Les chambres sont biens, conformes aux photos. L'hôtel est propre et neuf.
Le spa n'est pas mal, les masseuse sont pro. Les huiles sentent très bon !
Tous les soirs sont organisées des soirées à thème (quand elles ont lieux, 3 soirées annulées sur une semaine sans que ce soit annoncé) avec en première partie des chanteurs. Il s'agit peut être des seuls bons points.
Par contre,
Les cocktails ne sont pas des cocktails mais des préparations liquides infâmes. En une semaine j'ai essayé de tous les goûter et les regouter en espérant que ce ne soit qu'une erreur du barman mais non. Ils sont vraiment immondes.
La nourriture dans le restaurant buffet est assez bonne mais rien d'exceptionnel, il ne faut pas être exigeant, les desserts par contre sont très moyens.
Concernant le personnel, les serveurs et les réceptionnistes sont gentils et essayent de faire de leur mieux mais la qualité du service est moyenne. On a dû attendre parfois jusqu'à 30 minutes pour avoir une table, ou même un verre d'eau. Attendre un verre d'eau en pleine chaleur, sous 40° c'est vraiment pas top. Les bouteilles devraient au moins être donné en arrivant.
L'expérience n'a pas été désastreuse. J'en garderais un bon souvenir mais l'hôtel ne vaut pas du tout ses 5 étoiles... Plutôt 2-3 au maximum.
Je reviendrais sûrement un jour à Marrakech mais pas dans cet hôtel.

Location overview

This upscale, all-inclusive hotel for adults only is 7 km from Bahia Palace and 14 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.
Lot B6, Zone de Zahrat, Marrakesh
Directions

About this hotel

This upscale, all-inclusive hotel for adults only is 7 km from Bahia Palace and 14 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport. …

The modern rooms provide minibars, safes, and tea and coffeemaking facilities, in addition to flat-screen TVs and free Wi-Fi. Some have swim-up access. The 1-bedroom suites have separate living rooms.

There are 3 restaurants, a snack cafe and a lobby lounge, in addition to a poolside bar. Other amenities consist of an outdoor pool, a fitness room and a spa.
